text: Lynne Whitehead is an England international lawn bowler. She was born in 1973 and won the bronze medal in the pairs with Amy Gowshall at the 2002 Commonwealth Games in Manchester. She bowls for the Norfolk Bowling Club and has won four National titles. ==References== Category:Living people Category:1973 births Category:English female bowls players Category:Commonwealth Games competitors for England Category:Bowls players at the 2002 Commonwealth Games Category:Commonwealth Games medallists in lawn bowls Category:Commonwealth Games bronze medallists for England
